    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@rayrutjes I think that when an `XMLHttpRequest` is done with the `withCredentials` flag, it sends the `Basic Auth` informations along with the request. And in that case, the server must reply with an exact url in the `Access-Control-Allow-Origin`, but we always respond with a wildcard `*`, which fails.\n\nSo, I'm pretty sure another library is adding those headers to requests done to our servers.\n",
