    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "In the Algolia JavaScript client, we have two paths. One for the front-end and one for the back-end (which is a valid separation in a non-Meteor context). They both share the same common core, but have a few special cases to handle in each environment. Like CORS for example. Back-end code does not care about CORS.\n\nFrom what we understand, Meteor is trying to use the back-end build in the front-end (through `browserify`), while it should use the specific front-end build to do that. I have no idea how Meteor handles this kind of things...\n",
